743; Manca, M., Ruggiu, D., Consequences of pelagic food web changes during a long-term lake oligotrophication process (1998) Limnol. Oceanogr., 43, pp. 1368-1373; Mcknight, D., Brakke, D.F., Mulholland, P.J., Freshwater ecosystems and climate change in North America (1996) Limnol. Oceanogr., 41, pp. 815-1149; Molinero, J.C., Anneville, O., Souissi, S., Lainé, L., Gerdeaux, D., Decadal changes in water temperature and ecological time series in Lake Geneva, Europe-relationship to Atlantic climate variability (2007) Clim. Res., 34, pp. 15-23. , doi:10.3354/cr034015; O'Reilly, C.M., Alin, S.R., Plisnier, P.-D., Cohen, A.S., Mckee, B.A., Climate change decreases aquatic ecosystem productivity of Lake Tanganyika, Africa (2003) Nature, 424, pp. 766-768. , doi:10.1038/nature01833; Raven, J.A., Geider, R.J., Temperature and algal growth (1988) New Phytol., 110, pp. 441-461. , doi:10.1111/j.1469-8137.1988.tb00282.x; Rhee, G.I., Gotham, J., The effects of environmental factors on phytoplankton growth: Temperature and interactions of temperature with nutrient limitations (1981) Limnol. Oceanogr., 26, pp. 635-648; (1989) Lake Restoration by Reduction of Nutrient Loading: Expectations, Experiences and Extrapolations, , SAS, H. [ED.]. Academia Verlag Richarz; Schindler, D.W., Effects of climatic warming on lakes of the central boreal forest (1990) Science, 250, pp. 967-970. , doi:10.1126/science.250.4983.967; Smith, V.H., Light and nutrient dependence of photosynthesis by algae (1983) J. Phycol., 19, p. 306313. , doi:11111/j.00223646.1983.00306.x; Staehr, P.A., Sand-Jensen, K., Seasonal changes in temperature and nutrient control of photosynthesis, respiration and growth of natural phytoplankton communities (2006) Freshw. Biol., 51, pp. 249-262. , doi:10.1111/j.13652427.2005.01490.x; Steeman-Nielsen, E., The use of radio-active carbon for measuring organic production in the sea (1952) J. Cons. Int. Explor. Mer., 18, pp. 117-140; Strickland, J.D.H., Parsons, T.W., A practical hand